FBIS3-33496 "drlat037_g_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 Guatemala State Workers Occupy National Palace; Demand Wage Increase PA2302192194 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1813 GMT 23 Feb 94 PA2302192194 Mexico City NOTIMEX Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Guatemala City, 23 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- Today, approximately 40 state employees occupied the Guatemalan National Palace while hundreds have surrounded the Government House to demand a 40 percent salary increase. The move to occupy to palace, headed by Armando Sanchez, secretary general of the National Federation of State Workers Unions of Guatemala [FENASTEG], is part of several pressure measures being carried out by the workers, who initiated a 72-hour strike today. Sanchez warned that unless President Ramiro de Leon Carpio holds an "urgent" meeting with the workers, they will not leave the Presidential Palace. The workers at the palace are shouting: "We are not leaving." The presidential guard has been increased in and around the palace but so far there has been no altercations.
